46 template <class Key, class T> class Map
47 {
48 public:
49#ifndef DO_NOT_DOCUMENT
50#ifdef WANT_CLASS_INSTANTIATION_OF_MAP
51 // Some STL implementations get snippy over the use of the
52 // class keyword to distinguish different templates; Sun Studio
53 // in particular finds multiple specializations in certain rare
54 // cases and complains about that. GCC doesn't seem to mind,
55 // and uses the typedefs further below without the class keyword.
56 // Not all the specializations of Map can use the class keyword
57 // (when T is not actually a class type), so don't apply this
58 // generally.
59 using Iterator = typename std::map<class Key, class T>::iterator;
60 using ConstIterator = typename std::map<class Key, class T>::const_iterator;
61#else
62 using Iterator = typename std::map<Key, T>::iterator;
63 using ConstIterator = typename std::map<Key, T>::const_iterator;
64#endif
65#endif
